# Testing & Documentation Requirements

Every code change to this Terraform provider MUST include corresponding test updates and documentation updates. Never consider a task complete until both are done.

## Testing

- **Every new resource or data source** must have a CRUD test in `internal/provider/resource_test.go` (or `datasource_test.go`).
- **Every modification to an existing resource or data source** must update or extend its existing tests to cover the change.
- Follow the project's established test pattern:
  1. Create a `newMockAPIServer()` with `mock.On(...)` handlers for the relevant API endpoints.
  2. Use `resource.UnitTest` with `testProtoV6ProviderFactories(mock.URL())`.
  3. Include `TestStep` entries that verify all managed attributes via `resource.TestCheckResourceAttr`.
- Test names follow the convention `TestAcc<ResourceName>Resource_CRUD`.
- Test helper utilities live in `internal/provider/testutils_test.go`; reuse them.
- After writing tests, run `go test ./internal/provider/ -run <TestName> -v` to verify they pass.

## Documentation

- All end-user documentation lives in `docs/index.md`.
- **Every new resource or data source** must be added to the Table of Contents and have a full section with:
  - A description of what it manages.
  - An example HCL usage block.
  - An attribute reference table listing all arguments and read-only attributes.
- **Every modification** (new field, removed field, changed behavior) must update the relevant section in `docs/index.md` to reflect the change.

## Checklist (apply after every change)

1. Code change implemented.
2. Tests added or updated — and passing.
3. `docs/index.md` updated to reflect the change.
